definitions: An overtone accompanying a fundamental tone at a fixed interval, produced by vibration of a string, column of air, etc. in an exact fraction of its length.
A note produced on a musical instrument as an overtone, e.g. by lightly touching a string while sounding it.
A component frequency of an oscillation or wave.
A division of the zodiacal circle by a specified number, used in the interpretation of a birth chart.
